Lily Engelmaier By Danielle Tullo Feb 22, 2017 Kate Englemair, a Starbucks-loving 22-year-old from Georgia, just went where no basic woman has gone before. Joining the Belly Art Project â€” a book that encourages moms to support moms and put artwork on their pregnant stomachs â€” Kate had a Starbucks-themed maternity photoshoot. The photos are amazing. Advertisement - Continue Reading Below Due to have a boy on Feb. 28, Kate is a recent college graduate that runs a blog called A Brave Mess , where she writes about becoming a new single mother. She told Cosmopolitan.com she wanted her maternity shoot to be special. "I knew I wanted to do something unique that would stand out as well as represent me, and I guess my basic-ness." A post shared by Kate ðŸ’‹ (@abravemess) on Feb 20, 2017 at 6:55am PST With that in mind, Engelmair had a friend stencil out her stomach to look like the Starbucks siren and helped her paint. Then she went to Starbucks where her sister took her photos for a full-blown Starbucks maternity shoot. See the beautiful photos below: Lily Engelmaier
